          "author": "greptile-apps",
          "body": "<a href=\"#\"><img alt=\"P1\" src=\"https://greptile-static-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/badges/p1.svg?v=9\" align=\"top\"></a> **Archive path matching can include files from nested `registry/` directories**\n\n`components.iter().position(…)` finds the *first* path component named `\"registry\"` at any depth, not only the immediate child of the top-level prefix. For a tar entry like `mise-main/e2e/registry/tool.toml` the match would succeed (`registry_index = 2`, `components.len() = 4`, condition `4 != 4` is false), so the file would be processed as a registry tool named `\"tool\"`. Any TOML fixture under a `registry/` subdirectory — test data, documentation examples, etc. — would either produce a spurious tool definition in the floating registry or abort parsing entirely with an unrelated error, silently degrading to the baked registry. Adding `registry_index != 1` to the depth guard restricts extraction to files directly under the single top-level prefix directory.\n\n<a href=\"https://app.greptile.com/ide/claude-code?prompt=This%20is%20a%20comment%20left%20during%20a%20code%20review.%0APath%3A%20src%2Fregistry.rs%0ALine%3A%20199-209%0A%0AComment%3A%0A**Archive%20path%20matching%20can%20include%20files%20from%20nested%20%60registry%2F%60%20directories**%0A%0A%60components.iter%28%29.position%28%E2%80%A6%29%60%20finds%20the%20*first*%20path%20component%20named%20%60%22registry%22%60%20at%20any%20depth%2C%20not%20only%20the%20immediate%20child%20of%20the%20top-level%20prefix.%20For%20a%20tar%20entry%20like%20%60mise-main%2Fe2e%2Fregistry%2Ftool.toml%60%20the%20match%20would%20succeed%20%28%60registry_index%20%3D%202%60%2C%20%60components.len%28%29%20%3D%204%60%2C%20condition%20%604%20!%3D%204%60%20is%20false%29%2C%20so%20the%20file%20would%20be%20processed%20as%20a%20registry%20tool%20named%20%60%22tool%22%60.%20Any%20TOML%20fixture%20under%20a%20%60registry%2F%60%20subdirectory%20%E2%80%94%20test%20data%2C%20documentation%20examples%2C%20etc.%20%E2%80%94%20would%20either%20produce%20a%20spurious%20tool%20definition%20in%20the%20floating%20registry%20or%20abort%20parsing%20entirely%20with%20an%20unrelated%20error%2C%20silently%20degrading%20to%20the%20baked%20registry.%20Adding%20%60registry_index%20!%3D%201%60%20to%20the%20depth%20guard%20restricts%20extraction%20to%20files%20directly%20under%20the%20single%20top-level%20prefix%20directory.%0A%0AHow%20can%20I%20resolve%20this%3F%20If%20you%20propose%20a%20fix%2C%20please%20make%20it%20concise.&repo=jdx%2Fmise&pr=10971&platform=github\"><picture><source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\" srcset=\"https://greptile-static-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/badges/FixInClaudeDark.svg?v=6\"><source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: light)\" srcset=\"https://greptile-static-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/badges/FixInClaude.svg?v=6\"><img alt=\"Fix in Claude Code\" src=\"https://greptile-static-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/badges/FixInClaude.svg?v=6\"></picture></a>",
