          "body": "<a href=\"#\"><img alt=\"P1\" src=\"https://greptile-static-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/badges/p1.svg?v=9\" align=\"top\"></a> **Download blocks the calling thread, including Tokio worker threads**\n\n`std::thread::spawn(…).join()` blocks the thread that first dereferences `REGISTRY` for the entire HTTP download (potentially several seconds). The baked registry used to be a compile-time `static` with zero-cost first access; now the first access with `registry_floating = true` can block a Tokio worker thread. Because `REGISTRY` is accessed in many synchronous helpers that are called from async code (e.g., `shorts_for_full`, `is_trusted_plugin`, `RegistryTool::backends`), there is no guarantee the blocking happens outside the Tokio executor. On a `current_thread` runtime the single worker thread is suspended for the whole download, stalling all concurrent tasks. Even on the multi-threaded scheduler this reduces available concurrency during startup.\n\n<a href=\"https://app.greptile.com/ide/claude-code?prompt=This%20is%20a%20comment%20left%20during%20a%20code%20review.%0APath%3A%20src%2Fregistry.rs%0ALine%3A%20158-183%0A%0AComment%3A%0A**Download%20blocks%20the%20calling%20thread%2C%20including%20Tokio%20worker%20threads**%0A%0A%60std%3A%3Athread%3A%3Aspawn%28%E2%80%A6%29.join%28%29%60%20blocks%20the%20thread%20that%20first%20dereferences%20%60REGISTRY%60%20for%20the%20entire%20HTTP%20download%20%28potentially%20several%20seconds%29.%20The%20baked%20registry%20used%20to%20be%20a%20compile-time%20%60static%60%20with%20zero-cost%20first%20access%3B%20now%20the%20first%20access%20with%20%60registry_floating%20%3D%20true%60%20can%20block%20a%20Tokio%20worker%20thread.%20Because%20%60REGISTRY%60%20is%20accessed%20in%20many%20synchronous%20helpers%20that%20are%20called%20from%20async%20code%20%28e.g.%2C%20%60shorts_for_full%60%2C%20%60is_trusted_plugin%60%2C%20%60RegistryTool%3A%3Abackends%60%29%2C%20there%20is%20no%20guarantee%20the%20blocking%20happens%20outside%20the%20Tokio%20executor.%20On%20a%20%60current_thread%60%20runtime%20the%20single%20worker%20thread%20is%20suspended%20for%20the%20whole%20download%2C%20stalling%20all%20concurrent%20tasks.%20Even%20on%20the%20multi-threaded%20scheduler%20this%20reduces%20available%20concurrency%20during%20startup.%0A%0AHow%20can%20I%20resolve%20this%3F%20If%20you%20propose%20a%20fix%2C%20please%20make%20it%20concise.&repo=jdx%2Fmise&pr=10971&platform=github\"><picture><source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\" srcset=\"https://greptile-static-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/badges/FixInClaudeDark.svg?v=6\"><source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: light)\" srcset=\"https://greptile-static-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/badges/FixInClaude.svg?v=6\"><img alt=\"Fix in Claude Code\" src=\"https://greptile-static-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/badges/FixInClaude.svg?v=6\"></picture></a>",
