      "body": "<h3>Greptile Summary</h3>\n\nThis PR adds opt-in `registry_floating` (default off) and `registry_cache_ttl` (default 1h) so users on slow-updating distros can consume current mise shorthand and aqua registry metadata without replacing their mise binary. When enabled, the mise registry is fetched from the `jdx/mise` main tarball, cached under the mise cache dir, and parsed into a runtime `Registry` with the baked snapshot serving as fallback; the aqua path prepends the official aqua-registry URL and converts download errors into soft misses that fall through to the baked registry.\n\n- **`src/registry.rs`** \\u2014 converts `REGISTRY` from a compile-time `static` to a `LazyLock`, adds tar archive download/parse logic, and introduces a `RegistryLookup` enum to handle both PHF static maps and runtime `HashMap`s.\n- **`src/aqua/aqua_registry_wrapper.rs`** \\u2014 adds `fallback_on_error` per downloaded registry source and a `configured_registry_urls` path that injects the official aqua URL when floating mode is active.\n- **`settings.toml` / `schema/mise.json`** \\u2014 wire up the two new settings with docs, env vars, and schema entries.\n\n<h3>Confidence Score: 3/5</h3>\n\nSafe to merge with the floating feature disabled (the default); enabling registry_floating exposes the two logic issues in src/registry.rs.\n\nThe archive path matcher uses position() to find the first path component named registry at any depth, so a nested registry/*.toml file in the archive could either inject a spurious tool or abort the whole floating-registry parse. Separately, the first deref of REGISTRY with floating enabled runs a blocking thread::join that can stall a Tokio worker thread for the entire HTTP round-trip. Both issues only affect users who opt in to registry_floating = true, so the default baked path is unaffected.\n\nsrc/registry.rs — the archive path matching logic in parse_registry_archive and the blocking download path in download_registry_archive.\n\n<h3>Important Files Changed</h3>\n\n\n\n\n| Filename | Overview |\n|----------|----------|\n| src/registry.rs | Core change: converts REGISTRY from a compile-time static to a LazyLock that can download and parse a floating tarball. Contains two issues: archive path matching can accidentally pull in files from any nested `registry/` directory, and the download path blocks the calling thread (including Tokio workers) via thread::join. |\n| src/aqua/aqua_registry_wrapper.rs | Adds `fallback_on_error` field to DownloadedRegistry and appends the official aqua URL when registry_floating is set. Logic and tests look correct; fallback converts hard errors into Ok(None) so the baked registry can be tried next. |\n| src/config/settings.rs | Adds registry_cache_ttl() following the same .unwrap() pattern used by aqua_registry_cache_ttl(). Clean, consistent addition. |\n| build.rs | Wraps generated PHF map in RegistryLookup::Static(…) to match the new enum variant. Trivial, correct change. |\n| settings.toml | Adds registry_floating (Bool, default false) and registry_cache_ttl (Duration, optional, default 1h) settings with matching env vars and documentation. |\n| schema/mise.json | Schema entries for the two new settings; correctly typed and positioned. |\n| docs/registry.md | New \"Floating registries\" section clearly describes the opt-in behavior, fallback, and cache semantics. |\n| docs/dev-tools/backends/aqua.md | Brief documentation addition pointing users to the registry_floating setting and the new Floating registries section. |\n\n\n<!-- greptile_other_comments_section -->\n\n<a href=\"https://app.greptile.com/ide/claude-code?prompt=Fix%20the%20following%202%20code%20review%20issues.%20Work%20through%20them%20one%20at%20a%20time%2C%20proposing%20concise%20fixes.%0A%0A---%0A%0A%23%23%23%20Issue%201%20of%202%0Asrc%2Fregistry.rs%3A199-209%0A**Archive%20path%20matching%20can%20include%20files%20from%20nested%20%60registry%2F%60%20directories**%0A%0A%60components.iter%28%29.position%28%E2%80%A6%29%60%20finds%20the%20*first*%20path%20component%20named%20%60%22registry%22%60%20at%20any%20depth%2C%20not%20only%20the%20immediate%20child%20of%20the%20top-level%20prefix.%20For%20a%20tar%20entry%20like%20%60mise-main%2Fe2e%2Fregistry%2Ftool.toml%60%20the%20match%20would%20succeed%20%28%60registry_index%20%3D%202%60%2C%20%60components.len%28%29%20%3D%204%60%2C%20condition%20%604%20!%3D%204%60%20is%20false%29%2C%20so%20the%20file%20would%20be%20processed%20as%20a%20registry%20tool%20named%20%60%22tool%22%60.%20Any%20TOML%20fixture%20under%20a%20%60registry%2F%60%20subdirectory%20%E2%80%94%20test%20data%2C%20documentation%20examples%2C%20etc.%20%E2%80%94%20would%20either%20produce%20a%20spurious%20tool%20definition%20in%20the%20floating%20registry%20or%20abort%20parsing%20entirely%20with%20an%20unrelated%20error%2C%20silently%20degrading%20to%20the%20baked%20registry.%20Adding%20%60registry_index%20!%3D%201%60%20to%20the%20depth%20guard%20restricts%20extraction%20to%20files%20directly%20under%20the%20single%20top-level%20prefix%20directory.%0A%0A%23%23%23%20Issue%202%20of%202%0Asrc%2Fregistry.rs%3A158-183%0A**Download%20blocks%20the%20calling%20thread%2C%20including%20Tokio%20worker%20threads**%0A%0A%60std%3A%3Athread%3A%3Aspawn%28%E2%80%A6%29.join%28%29%60%20blocks%20the%20thread%20that%20first%20dereferences%20%60REGISTRY%60%20for%20the%20entire%20HTTP%20download%20%28potentially%20several%20seconds%29.%20The%20baked%20registry%20used%20to%20be%20a%20compile-time%20%60static%60%20with%20zero-cost%20first%20access%3B%20now%20the%20first%20access%20with%20%60registry_floating%20%3D%20true%60%20can%20block%20a%20Tokio%20worker%20thread.%20Because%20%60REGISTRY%60%20is%20accessed%20in%20many%20synchronous%20helpers%20that%20are%20called%20from%20async%20code%20%28e.g.%2C%20%60shorts_for_full%60%2C%20%60is_trusted_plugin%60%2C%20%60RegistryTool%3A%3Abackends%60%29%2C%20there%20is%20no%20guarantee%20the%20blocking%20happens%20outside%20the%20Tokio%20executor.%20On%20a%20%60current_thread%60%20runtime%20the%20single%20worker%20thread%20is%20suspended%20for%20the%20whole%20download%2C%20stalling%20all%20concurrent%20tasks.%20Even%20on%20the%20multi-threaded%20scheduler%20this%20reduces%20available%20concurrency%20during%20startup.%0A%0A&repo=jdx%2Fmise&pr=10971&platform=github\"><picture><source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\" srcset=\"https://greptile-static-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/badges/FixAllInClaudeDark.svg?v=6\"><source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: light)\" srcset=\"https://greptile-static-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/badges/FixAllInClaude.svg?v=6\"><img alt=\"Fix All in Claude Code\" src=\"https://greptile-static-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/badges/FixAllInClaude.svg?v=6\"></picture></a>\n\n<sub>Reviews (1): Last reviewed commit: [\"fix(registry): address floating registry...\"](https://github.com/jdx/mise/commit/14d5f218c04ebe2434b3552f699ec953cebc694f) | [Re-trigger Greptile](https://app.greptile.com/api/retrigger?id=43915936)</sub>",
